12. Timing: Min vs. Max Estimates
Suggestion	Detailed Description
Three-Tier Timing	Every step gets three time estimates: minHours (best case, experienced learner), typicalHours (average learner), maxHours (worst case, completely new to the topic). These are returned by the AI during generation.
Explanation Field	Each step includes a brief explanation of what determines the range. Example: "If you already know Node.js basics, you'll fly through this in 2 hours. If you're new to backend development, expect 6 hours to learn HTTP concepts alongside Express."
Profile-Based Default	The system looks at the user's profile. If the profile shows experience in related areas, it defaults to showing minHours. If the profile shows no experience, it defaults to showing maxHours. If unknown, it shows typicalHours. The user can always hover to see all three.
Tooltip Display	Hovering over the time estimate shows a tooltip with all three tiers and the explanation. This provides transparency without cluttering the UI.
Roadmap Header Range	At the top of big roadmaps, show a range: "⏱️ 3-6 months (min: 3mo, typical: 5mo, max: 8mo)". This sets honest expectations from the start and acknowledges that timelines vary.
